      <child nodeId="node-193"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-193">
    <command xml:space="preserve">leave</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">I could leave, but to where? I should probably read my cases first.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-194"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-194">
    <command xml:space="preserve">read cases</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">There are 2 cases here. Another couple just like my parents, found in Bingo Street... and a judge killed in his own chambers. He was working on some case about a cosmetics company. Before I leave though I should probably read these with more detail.&#x000A;&#x000A;The first case happened a week ago... they were found dead in a trash can. According to the police report, they had very peculiar injuries... it looks like they fought with the attacker.&#x000A;As for the second case, it was just delivered to me. The body is still in the courthouse, so I should head there soon. Judge Richard was found dead in his chambers found with a knife in his head. A judge can get a lot of enemies, but he was only working on one case at the time... I should go there.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-195"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-195">
    <command xml:space="preserve">read cases</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">The first case happened a week ago... they were found dead in a trash can. According to the police report, they had very peculiar injuries... it looks like they fought with the attacker.&#x000A;As for the second case, it was just delivered to me. The body is still in the courthouse, so I should head there soon. Judge Richard was found dead in his chambers found with a knife in his head. A judge can get a lot of enemies, but he was only working on one case at the time... I should go there.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
